<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards 2, United 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Tony Meola extended his Major League
Soccer-record shutout streak to 525 minutes as the Kansas City
Wizards beat D.C. United 2-0 on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   The former U.S. national team goalkeeper made only two saves in
recording his league-leading eighth shutout of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Kerry Zavagnin and Miklos Molnar scored second-half goals to
help the Wizards improve to 8-0-2. D.C. United dropped to 2-8-1.
</P>
<P>
   Zavagnin opened the scoring in the 73rd minute off a pass from
Preki. Molnar added his sixth goal of the season in the 79th
minute, connecting from 7 yards on a pass from Chris Henderson.
</P>
<P>
   The teams combined for six yellow cards and 52 fouls, the
third-highest total in MLS history.
</P>
</TEXT>
