<HEADLINE> Navy suspends four after sailor's drowning  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WEST MILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Four sailors assigned to the submarine
training unit at the Kenneth A. Kesselring Navy site have been
suspended following an alcohol-related boating accident that left
one sailor missing and presumed drowned.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Williams, 19, James Orms, 19, Denis Rees, 19, and Gregg
Cissell, 20, have been suspended from training, Lt. Commander
George Saroch told the Times Union of Albany.
</P>
<P>
   Williams and Charles Kegler, a 21-year-old sailor, were
suspended because they face criminal charges of providing alcohol
to minors. Cissell and Rees were suspended because they are
undergoing medical counseling. Orms has been charged with a boat
navigation violation.
</P>
<P>
   Saroch said the Navy is still determining what, if any,
disciplinary action will be taken against the sailors. A sixth
sailor, 20-year-old Matthew Weller, remains in training.
</P>
<P>
   The sailors and an 18-year-old female friend were on Saratoga
Lake at 3 a.m. Saturday, May 6 after a day of drinking when their
14-foot rowboat capsized. Aaron W. Binkerd, 19, of Indiana, is
missing and presumed drowned.
</P>
</TEXT>
