<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-18 12:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Up 24; Nasdaq Down 67  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed in quiet trading today as
investors sought direction in a market facing rising interest rates
and a dearth of significant economic news.
</P>
<P>
   ''The market is just marking time,'' said Alan Ackerman, senior
vice president at Fahnestock &AMP; Co. in New York. ''We have buyers
and sellers just waiting it out for the time being.''
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 23.65 at 10,793.39.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were mixed. The Nasdaq composite index
was down 66.94 at 3,578.02, and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was
down 5.66 at 1,442.14.
</P>
<P>
   Sprint fell 1} to 56\. The Wall Street Journal reported today
that federal antitrust enforcers have recommended blocking WorldCom
Inc.'s $115 billion buyout of Sprint because it would violate
antitrust law. WorldCom shares fell 1{ to 40{.
</P>
<P>
   Lycos rose 5 5/64 to 62 11/16. After the close of trading
Wednesday, the company reported better-than-expected results for
its fiscal third quarter. Analysts said investors were pleased with
the earnings report, but remain wary of the stock due to concerns
about the proposed takeover of Lycos by Spain's Terra Networks SA.
</P>
<P>
   The broader market was fairly quiet as investors continued to
scout a new path in a market facing higher interest rates. The
Federal Reserve raised interest rates for the sixth time since June
on Tuesday, pushing the federal funds rate -- the interest that
banks charge each other -- to 6.5 percent, the highest level in nine
years.
</P>
<P>
   Escalating borrowing costs make it tougher to borrow money to
finance growth. Ultimately, that can cut into corporate profits.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have a lingering case of interest rate jitters,'' Ackerman
said. ''There are not many who believe the Fed is near the end of
its rate hikes.''
</P>
<P>
   Still, financial stocks, which are vulnerable to interest rate
fluctuations, were modestly higher today. J.P. Morgan rose 2 to
134| and American Express rose 13/16 to 51}. Merrill Lynch rose 3
11/16 to 111 11/16.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-6 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 379.84 million
shares, compared with 388.56 million at the same time Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 4.29 to 495.37.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
