<HEADLINE> New Programs on Fox, UPN This Fall  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Thumbnail sketches of new programs to debut on Fox
this fall and
winter:
<TEXT>
<P>
   --''Boston Public,'' is by David E. Kelley, producer of ''Ally
McBeal'' and ''The Practice.'' It combines drama and comedy, and
focuses on the lives of teachers at a suburban Boston high school.
</P>
<P>
   --''Dark Angel,'' created by ''Titanic'' producer James Cameron,
is a science fiction series set in post-apocalyptic America that
follows a genetically-enhanced human prototype who is chased
through the Pacific Northwest by her military handlers.
</P>
<P>
   --''Fearsum,'' a science fiction series from a producer of ''The
Blair Witch Project,'' follows a webmaster who discovers through
the Internet that a twin he believed was dead is actually alive.
</P>
<P>
   --''The Lone Gunmen'' is a spinoff of ''The X-Files'' by creator
Chris Carter, following the computer-hacking conspiracy freaks as
they head out on their own.
</P>
<P>
   --''Night Visions,'' inspired by ''The Twilight Zone,'' is an
anthology series that incorporates horror, psychological drama and
supernatural adventure.
</P>
<P>
   --''The $treet'' is a drama about young Wall Street executives.
It is produced by Darren Star, who worked on ''Sex and the City''
and ''Beverly Hills 90210.''
</P>
<P>
   --A drama, without a title or cast yet, by ''ER'' creator Michael
Crichton.
</P>
<P>
   --''Don't Ask,'' stars John Goodman in a comedy about a gay dad
sharing a house in a Los Angeles suburb with a college friend and
their children.
</P>
<P>
   --''Schimmel,'' is a family comedy with comedian Robert Schimmel
starring as a father of two teen-age daughters who tries to get
through life without talking to his neighbors.
</P>
<P>
   Thumbnail sketches of new programs to debut on UPN this fall:
</P>
<P>
   --''Girlfriends,'' is a comedy about a successful black lawyer
and her friends.
</P>
<P>
   --''Freedom,'' created by ''The Matrix'' producer Joel Silver, is
a drama about a group of guerillas trying to liberate a future
America after a military coup.
</P>
<P>
   --''Level 9,'' is a drama about an elite FBI unit that fights
high-tech criminals.
</P>
</TEXT>
