<HEADLINE> Ronstadt Stalker May Be At It Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- A man convicted in 1998 of stalking singer
Linda Ronstadt is accused of doing it again.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors say 55-year-old Bernie Salazar Ortiz sent letters
and a package to Ronstadt's brother Michael at his Tucson-area home
between Nov. 9 and April 30. In the package: a 59-page handwritten
letter, a gold bracelet with jewels, a gold cross and three
cassette tapes.
</P>
<P>
   Ortiz was arrested May 6 outside an arena west of Phoenix hours
before Ronstadt was scheduled to perform.
</P>
