<HEADLINE> Franks Named Mideast Command Chief  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Army Lt. Gen. Tommy R. Franks has been
nominated to become commander in chief of the U.S. Central Command,
responsible for the Middle East and parts Africa, the Pentagon
announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Franks is now commanding the Third U.S. Army at Fort McPherson,
Ga.
</P>
<P>
   He will be promoted to general and succeed Marine Corps Gen.
Tony Zinni, pending Senate confirmation, spokesman Ken Bacon said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   He didn't say what Zinni's future plans are following the
routinely scheduled change of command.
</P>
