<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mississippi gives nod to MGM Grand's purchase of Mirage, Beau Rivage casino </HEADLINE>
By MATT MOORE
<TEXT>
<P>
   JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Mississippi gaming regulators have given
unanimous approval to MGM Grand Inc.'s acquisition of Mirage
Resorts Inc.
</P>
<P>
   The Gaming Commission granted MGM Grand the regulatory approval
Thursday after investigating the company's corporate officers,
including director Kirk Kerkorian, and examining all of its
holdings and subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
   The $6.4 billion merger will give MGM ownership of the Beau
Rivage and its first casino in Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   Speaking to gaming commissioners, Kerkorian said the first trip
he took to see Mirage's properties was to the casino in Biloxi.
Kerkorian holds a 60-percent stake in MGM.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was totally impressed with the people and the hotel. I just
couldn't believe it,'' Kerkorian said of the recent trip.
</P>
<P>
   Opened in 1999, the $700 million, 1,800-room Beau Rivage is
regarded as the largest and most luxurious casino in Mississippi.
</P>
<P>
   But it has suffered from lingering criticism that its luxury is
too upscale for Southern customers.
</P>
<P>
   ''The property is probably too much for that market on a lot of
different levels,'' said Daniel Davila, senior leisure and
entertainment analyst with Hibernia Southcoast Capital in New
Orleans. ''There is clearly a need for that type of product, but
not along the scope to which Mirage built it.''
</P>
<P>
   John Redmond, co-CEO at MGM, said the company will market the
resort to a cross-segment of customers, and use its other resorts
around the United States as promotional tools for the Beau Rivage,
too.
</P>
<P>
   ''It makes sense to look at this property as something that we
would want to cater to all market segments, as opposed to just
one,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   MGM co-CEO Daniel Wade said the company doesn't plan to change
the name of Beau Rivage or its management team. Jeff Dahl, Beau
Rivage's recently named president, will stay on in that position.
</P>
<P>
   Wade said the casino has been ''kind of undernourished a little
bit and we need to grow it a little more and that's our intent.''
</P>
<P>
   MGM Chairman Terrence Lanni said ''Biloxi is a very important
market to us'' and has no plans to close Beau Rivage.
</P>
<P>
   Based in Las Vegas MGM owns 18 casinos in on three continents,
including the Las Vegas MGM Grand, the world's largest
hotel/casino. MGM had net income of more than $86 million on sales
of $1.3 billion for 1999. It employs more than 6,700 people.
</P>
<P>
   Mirage, also based in Las Vegas, has casinos in Nevada and Monte
Carlo and plans to build one in Atlantic City, N.J. It had earnings
of $110 million on sales $2.4 billion during 1999. It employs
nearly 30,000 people.
</P>
<P>
   At the close of trading Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange,
shares of MGM were down 44 cents to close at $33.12, a decline of
1.3 percent. Shares of Mirage held steady at $20.62.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: MGM Grand: http://www.mgmgrand.com
</P>
<P>
   Mirage Resorts: http:www.mirageresorts.com
</P>
<P>
   Mississippi Gaming Commission: http://www.msgaming.com
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
