<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NY Judge Arrested After Wife Stabbed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW HYDE PARK, N.Y. (AP) -- A judge was arrested Thursday after
allegedly stabbing his wife in the back during an argument at their
home.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Kowtna, 51, was taken into custody after police responded
to a domestic dispute call about 8:20 a.m., said Det. Sgt. John
Giambrone. He said the judge placed the call to police.
</P>
<P>
   Officers found Mary Gail Kowtna, 45, suffering from two stab
wounds to the upper left side of her back. She was in stable
condition, a hospital spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
   Kowtna was hospitalized for a psychological evaluation. Specific
charges against him were pending, Giambrone said.
</P>
<P>
   Kowtna has been a Nassau County Court judge since 1994, handling
criminal cases. He previously worked in the district attorney's
office, where his primary responsibility was fraud cases.
</P>
</TEXT>
