Sept. 2, 1998, killing all 229 passengers on board.
</P>
<P>
   The plane's manifest indicates that two kilograms of diamonds
and five kilograms of jewelry were aboard when it went down. The
valuables were never found.
</P>
<P>
   A Lloyd's spokesperson said they hope to begin the search this
summer.
