<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 3 HRs To Reach 539th  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit three home runs Thursday
night and moved past Mickey Mantle into eighth place on the career
list with 539.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire leads the majors with 17 homers this year.
</P>
<P>
   The St. Louis star broke a tie with Mantle when he connected for
No. 537, a three-run drive in the first inning off Philadelphia's
Curt Schilling.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire then hit a two-run homer into the upper deck in the
second inning. He connected for a two-run shot to center in the
eighth.
</P>
<P>
   It was his 64th multi-homer game, moving him into second place
ahead of Willie Mays. Babe Ruth is first with 72.
</P>
<P>
   It was McGwire's fifth three-homer game and first since hitting
three at Veterans Stadium on May 19, 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Next up for McGwire on the career home run list is former
Phillies star Mike Schmidt at 548.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire is 4-for-18 lifetime off Schilling with all four hits
being homers, including one on April 30.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire had been 0-for-6 with four strikeouts in the three-game
series against the Phillies.
</P>
</TEXT>
